"title": "8157: righteousness, as faith",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8157",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Full faith and trust make a person pleasing in the sight of God.</p>\n<h2>Human righteousness compared with God's righteousness</h2>\n<h3>Human beings cannot by themselves achieve righteousness in the sight of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:20\">ECC 7:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:20\">MAT 5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:2\">PRO 21:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:18\">DAN 9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:28\">MAT 23:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:15\">LUK 16:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9\">LUK 18:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:10\">ROM 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:20\">ROM 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:6-Phil3:7\">PHP 3:6–3:7</a></p>\n<h2>True righteousness is the result of the action of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3-Rom8:4\">ROM 8:3–8:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:24\">EPH 4:24</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:29\">1JN 2:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:13\">ROM 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:16-Rom6:20\">ROM 6:16–6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:10\">ROM 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:5\">GAL 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:9\">EPH 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:11\">PHP 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:11\">HEB 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:18\">JAS 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:10\">1JN 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Faith pleases God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:6\">HEB 11:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:23\">1SA 26:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:10\">PSA 32:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:4\">PSA 40:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:12\">PSA 84:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:30-Ps106:31\">PSA 106:30–106:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:7\">JER 17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:4\">HAB 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:38\">HEB 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:4\">HEB 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:7\">HEB 11:7</a></p>\n<h2>Righteousness and faith in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>It is God-given and not the result of human effort</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:17\">ROM 1:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8-Phil3:9\">PHP 3:8–3:9</a></strong> <em>Paul is contrasting this righteousness with his own previous efforts.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:39\">ACT 13:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21\">ROM 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:27-Rom3:28\">ROM 3:27–3:28</a> <em>It is apparent that faith is not regarded as another kind of “work” which earns salvation</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:1-Rom4:8\">ROM 4:1–4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:17\">ROM 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:30-Rom9:31\">ROM 9:30–9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:11-Gal3:12\">GAL 3:11–3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Faith is centred on Jesus Christ and what he has accomplished</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>“justified” means “declared righteous” in a legal sense.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:21–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:18-Rom4:25\">ROM 4:18–4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:6-Rom10:10\">ROM 10:6–10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:9\">GAL 3:6–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Saving faith is not mere belief, but acting on the basis of that belief</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:21-Jas2:24\">JAS 2:21–2:24</a></p>",
